This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with semantic segmentation, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture, which involves learning adaptive receptive fields, and this is a common research area in computer vision. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. 

The paper's focus on developing a new network architecture that can adaptively capture free form dense semantic contexts suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. 

Finally, the paper's use of two representative semantic segmentation datasets suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
